text: Chulalongkorn (Thai: จุฬาลงกรณ์, 20 September 1853 – 23 October 1910) was the fifth monarch of Siam under the House of Chakri, titled Rama V. He was known to the Siamese of his time as Phra Phuttha Chao Luang (พระพุทธเจ้าหลวง, the Royal Buddha). ==References== Category:1853 births Category:1910 deaths Category:Monarchs of Thailand Category:Chakri dynasty Category:20th-century Thai monarchs Category:19th-century Thai monarchs
